ideological party, a conservative party. That's

00:38:30.390 --> 00:38:38.190
why there's almost no Republicans in the Northeast,
in New England, anymore. And then, no Democrats

00:38:38.190 --> 00:38:44.260
anymore in the South. There's about three
or four remaining dinosaurs in the Republican

00:38:44.260 --> 00:38:53.650
Party, like Olympia Snow, and a couple others
in New England. And they will lose their seats

00:38:53.650 --> 00:38:54.650
shortly.

00:38:54.650 --> 00:38:59.890
So the Republican Party is a party that is
answerable to its activist wing. And if they

00:38:59.890 --> 00:39:06.520
don't toe the line, they're shot down and
the Democrats are not. The Democrats are an

00:39:06.520 --> 00:39:10.530
establishment party, and by and large, a centrist
party. By and large, they're always trying

00:39:10.530 --> 00:39:16.150
to find what the swing voter wants and give
it to them and ask their activists just to

00:39:16.150 --> 00:39:18.050
keep quiet and wait their turn.

00:39:18.050 --> 00:39:23.830
And if you notice, Barack Obama and his advisors
are always making fun of Liberals and saying,

00:39:23.830 --> 00:39:28.570
"Oh, they're whining about not getting everything
they wanted." Whereas Republicans never do

00:39:28.570 --> 00:39:34.470
that. Republicans are very respectful on their
base, no matter now crazy they are. Now, in

00:39:34.470 --> 00:39:39.430
a parliamentary, parliamentary system, you
would want parties like Republican parties

00:39:39.430 --> 00:39:43.730
so that everybody's interest could be fairly
represented.

00:39:43.730 --> 00:39:52.010
So if I happen to have this particular group
of -- like, in Israel you've got all these

00:39:52.010 --> 00:39:56.430
little parties that represent very particular
points of view. You've got like, a dozen parties.

00:39:56.430 --> 00:40:03.890
And the only, the only -- they each get to
get five percent. They have a threshold of

00:40:03.890 --> 00:40:10.109
five percent to be seated in the Parliament.
But in our system, you've got a winner take

00:40:10.109 --> 00:40:18.609
all system where, where, where if you get
one vote more than the other side gets, you

00:40:18.609 --> 00:40:22.849
get all of the seats. You get, you get the
entire Presidency.

00:40:22.849 --> 00:40:28.359
You don't even need a majority. You just need
one vote more than anybody else. So it doesn't

00:40:28.359 --> 00:40:36.080
make any sense to have anything to try and
make your party as small and ideological as

00:40:36.080 --> 00:40:43.230
you can in terms of winning. You wanna have
a broad coalition to win and then fight it

00:40:43.230 --> 00:40:48.510
out once you've won. The problem with that,
and I think it's a clear problem for the Democrats,

00:40:48.510 --> 00:40:53.589
is that if you have all of these disparate
people with disagreements in your party, it's

00:40:53.589 --> 00:40:56.359
very hard to say what you stand for, right?

00:40:56.359 --> 00:41:00.069
So we know what Republicans believe in. We
know what Conservatives believe in. Small

00:41:00.069 --> 00:41:09.790
government, less taxes, fewer immigrants,
kick ass in the rest of the world, no making

00:41:09.790 --> 00:41:17.089
nice with other countries that give us a hard
time. But what do the Democrats believe? I

00:41:17.089 --> 00:41:23.940
don't think anybody can really explain it.
So because our politics are so personalized,

00:41:23.940 --> 00:41:25.810
people like to vote for the stronger sounding
person.

00:41:25.810 --> 00:41:30.770
You have to be really crazy to be too crazy
to get elected in this country if you're,

00:41:30.770 --> 00:41:34.970
if you sound like you know what you're talking
about. So the Republicans have actually stepped

00:41:34.970 --> 00:41:39.510
over, because of the Tea Party, they've managed
to step over that line a little bit in the

00:41:39.510 --> 00:41:45.040
last election. But I think that, it's my impression,
and this is just a feeling, this is just a

00:41:45.040 --> 00:41:48.900
feeling, but I think it's true, I've been
watching this stuff for 30, 40 years.

00:41:48.900 --> 00:41:53.119
I think Americans admire people who know what
they stand for, who can articulate it, and

00:41:53.119 --> 00:41:58.619
who can speak for it in a strong way without
hemming and hawing. And that's more important

00:41:58.619 --> 00:42:02.730
to them than whether or not they actually
agree with what the person's saying. Just

00:42:02.730 --> 00:42:05.980
that they vote much more on the strength of
personality than they do on the issues. They

00:42:05.980 --> 00:42:07.680
don't pay that much attention to the issues.

00:42:07.680 --> 00:42:12.980
So I think the Democrats will be much better
off with a stronger, more focused, more logical

00:42:12.980 --> 00:42:17.430
party than they are with the party they have
today, more like the Republicans. I think

00:42:17.430 --> 00:42:22.690
the Republicans make more sense. But you could
make an argument for the other side, and they

00:42:22.690 --> 00:42:24.171
might be right, too. It's a very tough question.
Thank you.

00:42:24.171 --> 00:42:26.480
